<h3>New Pet Skill</h3>
<p>Fire has dramatically changed since the level 49 summoned version.&nbsp; It's
now a wizard!&nbsp; It melees for only about half of the damage of 51 Earth
(which is odd, since wizard mobs hit just as hard as warrior mobs).&nbsp; It
casts level 12 - 20 wizard spells, including a shieldskin (a limited amount of
damage is absorbed).&nbsp; It no longer casts a powerful damage shield on
itself.&nbsp; Instead, it casts O'Keils Embers -- a very weak DS that does 3
points damage.</p>

<p>This pet has a few disadvantages: 1) it casts AoEs (it will wake up
mesmerized mobs), 2) its damage ability is mana bound (it doesn't have staying
power for long fights...although you can reclaim and summon a new one), 3) it
cannot tank.</p>

<p>It offers a few advantages: 1) it casts a stun and root (enstill)....a lot!,
2) it can AoE green cons like there's no tomorrow, 3) it is more interesting to
watch than the other pets.</p>

<p>All in all, I'm very happy to see a pet based on a wizard.&nbsp; However, the
pet isn't very smart nor capable.&nbsp; At this level of the game, a fire pet
based on the old model isn't necessary.&nbsp; I'd like to see Verant put more
thought into this pet.</p>

<p>May/June 2002 changes to mob caster AI and pets seem to have
resulted in an adjustment to the 52 (and 58) fire pet.&nbsp; Occasionally, the
fire pet will chain-cast Tishan's Clash (a stun).&nbsp; This can be a very
effective strategy against both caster and melee mobs.&nbsp; Several of these
pets in a group can effectively prevent a mob from doing much more than beg for
a quick and painless end.&nbsp; If you get a chain stunning fire pet (the
randomness may be pet level-based) you'll see it stun much more often than even
the Air pet.</p>

<p>I've got no proof of it, but I believe that magician summoned focus items
help.&nbsp; Give the pet a bracer and ring and it should cast faster and for
more damage.&nbsp; However, since log data does not show pet spell damage, I
can't be certain this is actually helpful.</p>

<p>Note: The Torch of Alna will not benefit pets over the 49th summon.&nbsp;
Since the fire pet has changed so dramatically, you may find yourself summoning
the 49 version from time to time.&nbsp; Keep the torch with you if you think
you'll make the 49 pet often enough.&nbsp; Only the Staff of Elemental Mastery:
Fire will act as a focus item on this and the 58 fire pet.</p>

<p><i>Historical Note: This pet used to cast Cancel Magic and Gate (when it got
hurt badly).&nbsp; I've not seen it cast either of these since the May
2002 change to mob caster AI.&nbsp; Verant has not made an official statement
on what spells are in the book of this pet.</i></p>

<h3>Bristlebane's Bundle</h3>
<p>This spell summons a party pack of ale, cake, a single use firework and a
bottle.&nbsp; The firework gives off the visual effect of a spell being
cast.&nbsp; The bottle makes the user spin around and around.&nbsp; Whee!</p>

<h3>More on Healing Your Pet</h3>
<p>Transon's Elemental Infusion is a great upgrade.&nbsp; It heals 556 damage
for 275 mana and also attempts to cure disease.&nbsp; However, don't let your
lower level heals get lost in your spell book.&nbsp; Renew Elements is great for
curing disease cheaply.&nbsp; Renew Summoning is great for a quick cover heal if
you need it -- it casts 30% faster.</p>

